                   <h1>Vannevar Bush Award</h1>
                    <p>
                  
                    <em>Honoring Exceptional Service to the Nation in Science and Technology </em></p>
                    <p></p>
					
                
			<hr class="gradient_one" align="left"/>
                   

                    <p>  <img src="/nsb/images/awards/bush-2-logo.png" alt="Vannevar Bush Award" align="right" height="136" width="140" />The Vannevar Bush Award honors <em>exceptional lifelong leaders in science and technology</em>. NSB established this award in 1980 in the memory of Vannevar Bush. Bush served as a science advisor to the US President during World War II, helped establish Federal funding for science and engineering as a national priority during peacetime, and was behind the creation of the National Science Foundation.</p>
					<p>Candidates for the Vannevar Bush Award must be U.S. citizens and meet two out of three selection criteria:</p>
                    <ul>
					<li><strong>Intellectual Merit</strong> – advanced and helped mold the frontiers of knowledge, technology, education</li>
					<li><strong>Public Service to the Nation</strong> – demonstrated distinguished public service to enhance the nation’s science and technology ecosystem</li>
					<li><strong>Societal Benefits</strong> – delivered benefits to the nation through science, technology, engineering, or mathematics.</li>
                    </ul>
					<p>View <a href="/nsb/awards/bush_recipients.jsp">previous award receipients</a>.</p>
                    <p>&nbsp;</p>
					<!--<p><strong>Nominations are closed for the 2023 awards. NSB will announce its 2023 Vannevar Bush and Science and Society Awards in spring of 2023.</strong></p>
                    <p style="color:red;"><a name="procedures" id="procedures"></a>NEW, EASY NOMINATION PROCESS!</p>
                    
                    <ol>
                      <li>By September 29, 2023, please submit 1 paragraph to highlight how the candidate meets two out of three of the criteria above.</li>
                      <li>For inquiries, please contact Nadine Lymn, <a href="mailto:nlymn@nsf.gov">nlymn@nsf.gov</a> or 703-292-2490.</li>
                    </ol>
					
					<p>That’s it! Winners will be notified no later than February 2024.</p
                   <br><br>
                    <h4>SUBMIT A NOMINATION</h4>
                    <p><iframe width="75%" height="1000" frameborder="0" src="https://app.smartsheetgov.com/b/form/09adfa88956749fd9d3af8f091bc94cc"></iframe><!--Please save all nomination documents as PDF or Word files and email them as attachments to: <a href="mailto:nsbawards@nsf.gov">nsbawards@nsf.gov</a>.                   
                    </p>-->
                    
                    <h4>INQUIRIES</h4>
                    <p>For questions concerning the awards, please contact Elizabeth Jeffers at <a href="mailto:ejeffers@nsf.gov">ejeffers@nsf.gov</a>, (703) 292-7496.<br />
                  </p>
                   <p>&nbsp; </p>
                
